The paper deals with the problem of finding F-free orderings of vertices in graphs, where F is a set of forbidden patterns. This problem is closely related to graph theory, combinatorics, and computational complexity, which are all covered by the arXiv categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Given the focus on graph theory and combinatorics, cs.DM and cs.DS are the most likely categories. However, the discussion of algorithms and computational complexity suggests that cs.CC is also a likely category. Finally, the mention of digraph ordering problems and bipartite versions of the problem suggests that cs.GT and cs.CG are also possible categories.
